viewpoint /ˈvjuːˌpɔɪnt/

(viewpoints) 

1. N-COUNT Someone's viewpoint is the way that they think about things in general, or the way they think about a particular thing. 视点 

例： The novel is shown from the girl's viewpoint. 这部小说是从那个女孩儿的视点展开的。 

2. N-COUNT A viewpoint is a place from which you can get a good view of something. 视角 

例： You have to know where to stand for a good viewpoint. 你得知道站在哪儿才会有好的视角。

</div>

